# Persona & Appearance Editor

## Overview
Build a no-code friendly Persona & Appearance Editor for ConverseForms that lets creators define and refine AI agents representing public forms. Each agent encapsulates a persona (tone, instructions, style guide, prohibited topics), an appearance profile (avatar URL, color scheme, chat bubble settings), and constrained behaviors (verbosity caps, disallowed responses). The system should support live preview via sandboxed LLM or deterministic simulator, and expose REST endpoints to update persona and appearance. The project includes three associated pages: Agent Detail / Publish Page, Agent Builder / Editor, and Public Chat Page (Agent URL). All components must be robust against null/undefined values and strictly adhere to the runtime safety rules described in the project context.

## Components to Build
1) Persona & Appearance Editor (Editor UI)
- Purpose: Core no-code interface to create/edit an agent.
